\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
拟线性单波方程
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Riemann!~ problem!~ for a single conservation law
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The disturbance of the initial discontinuity spreads at a finite speed,
 so there must be two undisturbed regions in the solution, in which 
\begin_inset Formula $U(x,t)$
\end_inset

 takes its initial value.
 These two undisturbed regions are connected by a disturbed region.
 Self-similarity implies that the interfaces of these regions are straight
 lines emanated from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
 So, the solution must have the following form:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<\lambda_{-}\\
U_{*} & x/t\in[\lambda_{-},\lambda_{+}]\\
U_{+} & x/t>\lambda_{+}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

in which
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda(U)=\pdv{F}{U}\qquad\lambda_{\pm}=\lambda(U_{\pm})
\]

\end_inset

Our task is to determine 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{*}$
\end_inset

, which is a function depends on 
\begin_inset Formula $x/t$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
激波 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!shock wave
\end_layout

\end_inset

If 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}>U_{+}$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}<0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}<U_{+}$
\end_inset

, we will have 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}>\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, which means the characteristic curves emanating from one half of the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

-axis will“run into”those emanating from the other half of the 
\begin_inset Formula $x$
\end_inset

-axis.
 In this case, a“ (shock wave)”separating the two families of parallel character
istic curves will emanate from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
 The speed of the shock wave is determined by the jump condition and the
 entropy condition
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u^{\Gamma}=\frac{F_{+}-F_{-}}{U_{+}-U_{-}}\qquad\lambda_{-}>u^{\Gamma}>\lambda_{+}
\]

\end_inset

is strictly satisfied.
 The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<u^{\Gamma}\\
\text{shock} & x/t=u^{\Gamma}\\
U_{+} & x/t>u^{\Gamma}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
膨胀波 If 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}>0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}<U_{+}$
\end_inset

, or 
\begin_inset Formula $\dv*{\lambda}{U}<0$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}>U_{+}$
\end_inset

, we will have 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}<\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, which means the two families of characteristic curves will“diverge”from
 each other.
 In this case, a fan-shaped“ (centered expansion wave)”separating the two
 families of parallel characteristic curves will start from 
\begin_inset Formula $(0,0)$
\end_inset

.
 The speed of the“ (wave head)”is 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, while that of the“ (wave tail)”is 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}$
\end_inset

.
 In the region between them, 
\begin_inset Formula $u(x,t)$
\end_inset

 is smooth enough to satisfy the PDE, which can be solved from the equation
 of characteristic curves:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
u(x,t)=\lambda^{-1}(x/t)\impliedby x/t=\lambda(u)
\]

\end_inset

where 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda^{-1}$
\end_inset

 means the inverse function of 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda$
\end_inset

.
 The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<\lambda_{-}\\
\text{expansion} & x/t\in\left[\lambda_{-},\lambda_{+}\right]\\
U_{+} & x/t>\lambda_{+}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
接触间断 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!contact ~
\end_layout

\end_inset

There might be such a case that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{-}=\lambda_{+}$
\end_inset

, even though 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{-}\ne U_{+}$
\end_inset

.
 In this case, there will be no mass/momentum/energy flowing across the
 discontinuity, thus it is called a“ (contact discontinuity)”.
 The speed of the contact discontinuity is the same as the left and right
 characteristic speed:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\lambda_{-}=u^{\Gamma}=\lambda_{+}
\]

\end_inset

The complete solution is then
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
U(x,t)=\begin{cases}
U_{-} & x/t<u^{\Gamma}\\
\text{contact} & x/t=u^{\Gamma}\\
U_{+} & x/t>u^{\Gamma}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

接触间断兼具激波与膨胀波的特性：
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
