\begin_layout Lemma
守恒律方程组的 Riemann 解具有自相似结构：
\begin_inset Formula $(x,t)$
\end_inset

 平面被 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 个基本波（激波、膨胀波、接触间断）划分为 
\begin_inset Formula $(m+1)$
\end_inset

 个扇形常值区域。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Proof
There are 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 characteristic fields, so the initial discontinuity will be carried by
 
\begin_inset Formula $m$
\end_inset

 elementary waves.
 Since the solution of an RP is self-similar, we can define the“ (slope)”as
 a new independent variable:
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\alpha\coloneqq x/t\implies\begin{cases}
\pdv*{t}=(\pdv*{\alpha}{t})(\dv*{\alpha})\\
\pdv*{x}=(\pdv*{\alpha}{x})(\dv*{\alpha})
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

PDE 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand eqref
reference "eq:multi_wave_quasilinear_system"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

 can be transformed into
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\left(\Matrix{A}-\alpha\Matrix{I}\right)\ket{\dv{U}{\alpha}}=\ket{0}
\]

\end_inset

which implies in smooth regions, either 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{\dv*{U}{\alpha}}=\ket{0}$
\end_inset

, which means 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U}$
\end_inset

 is constant, or 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha$
\end_inset

 is an eigenvalue of 
\begin_inset Formula $\Matrix{A}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{\dv*{U}{\alpha}}$
\end_inset

 is the corresponding right eigenvector.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Notation
Denote the slope on the right and left side of 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th elementary wave as 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}$
\end_inset

 respectively.
 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}=\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 cannot imply 
\begin_inset Formula $\ket{U(\alpha_{k-})}=\ket{U(\alpha_{k+})}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_deeper
\begin_layout Itemize
For shock waves, there are there 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}=\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For centered expansion waves, there are 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}<\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k\pm})=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
For contact discontinuities, there are there 
\begin_inset Formula $\alpha_{k-}=\alpha_{k+}$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $u^{\Gamma_{k}}=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lambda_{k}(\alpha_{k\pm})=\alpha_{k\pm}$
\end_inset

.
\end_layout

\end_deeper
\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Lemma
激波或膨胀波一定属于真正非线性的特征场，接触间断一定属于线性退化的特征场。
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Description
激波 
\begin_inset Index idx
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout
discontinuity!shock wave
\end_layout

\end_inset

If the 
\begin_inset Formula $k$
\end_inset

th characteristic field is genuinely nonlinear, there might be such a case
 that
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
